\pard\plain \ \f4\fs20\lang2057 {\fs28    }{\b\fs28 8. L. nivalis}{\fs28  Kit. in Schultes,}{\i\fs28  \'d6sterreichs Fl. }{\fs28 ed. 2, }{\b\fs28 1:}{\fs28  698 (1814). Caespitose, glabrous, with ciliate or serrulate leaves. Stems 5-20 cm, simple, not viscid. Basal leaves crowded, oblong-lanceolate to subspathulate; cauline 1 or 2 pairs, often linear. Flowers 1-3; pedicels equalling or shorter than calyx. Calyx 10-12 mm. Petal-limb purple or white, 2-lobed. Carpophore short. }{\i\fs28 Damp, stony places,}{\fs28  1800-2300}{\i\fs28  m. E. Carpathians}{\fs28  (}{\i\fs28 Muntii Rodnei}{\fs28 ). Rm.
