\pard \qc\ {\fs28  }{\b\fs28 27.            Petrocoptis}{\fs28             A. Braun
\par }{\fs24  By \'86W. Rothmahler (ed.1) revised by S.M. Walters (ed.2).
\par 
\par }
\pard \ {\fs28 Perennials, woody at the base, glabrous or nearly so, often glaucous and viscid above. Inflorescence cymose, 1- to 10-flowered. Epicalyx absent. Calyx conical-campanulate, 10-veined. Petals imbricate in bud, long-clawed; coronal scales present; stamens 10; styles 5 opposite the calyx-teeth; carpophore present. Seeds reniform, black, with a conspicuous strophiole consisting of a tuft of hairs at the hilum.
\par 
\par All species grow in crevices of calcareous rocks, mainly above 500 m, but occasionally in the lowlands.
\par 
\par Literature: W. Rothmaler,}{\i\fs28  Bot. Jahrb.}{\b\fs28  72}{\fs28 (}{\b\fs28 1}{\fs28 ): 117-130 (1941). H. Merxm\'fcller & J. Grau, }{\i\fs28 Collect. Bot.}{\fs28  (}{\i\fs28 Barcelona}{\fs28 ),}{\b\fs28  7:}{\fs28  787-797 (1968). P. Montserrat & J. Fern\'e1ndez Casas in S. Castroviejo et al. (eds.),}{\i\fs28  Flora Iberica}{\b\fs28  2:}{\fs28  304 312 (1990).
