\par 
\par    }{\b\fs28 3. P. hispanica}{\fs28  (Willk.) Pau,}{\i\fs28  Bol. Soc. Aragon. Ci. Nat.}{\b\fs28  15:}{\fs28  65 (1916) (}{\i\fs28 P.pyrenaica }{\fs28 var. }{\i\fs28 hispanica}{\fs28  Willk.). Plant with basal leaf-rosettes; stems up to 40(-60) cm. Basal leaves up to 8 cm, obovate glaucous, thick in texture, petiolate, not ciliate; lower cauline elliptical to ovate; upper suborbicular. Bracts 1-2\'b75 mm, scarious with green midrib. Calyx 6-8(-10) mm. Petals emarginate, white or pale pink. Seeds c. 1\'b75 mm, rather shining. 2n = 24. \bullet }{\i\fs28  W. & C. Pre-Pyrenees}{\fs28 . Hs.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs28 P. pseudoviscosa}{\fs28  Fern\'e1ndez Casas,}{\i\fs28  Cuad. Ci. Biol.}{\b\fs28  2:}{\fs28  44 (1973), described from the same region (gorge of R. Esera), is said to differ from }{\b\fs28 3}{\fs28  in the absence of leaf-rosettes and in the larger strophiole. It seems doubtfully distinct.
\par 
\par    }{\b\fs28 4. P. crassifolia}{\fs28  Rouy,}{\i\fs28  Ill. Pl. Eur. Rar. }{\b\fs28 4:}{\fs28  26 (1895) (incl. }{\i\fs28 P. montserratii}{\fs28  Fern\'e1ndez Casas). Plant with basal leaf-rosettes; stems up to 40(-80) cm. Basal leaves ovate-spathulate, glaucous, thick in texture, petiolate, not ciliate; cauline ovate-lanceolate. Bracts 2-5 mm, acuminate, more or less scarious. Calyx 8-12 mm. Petals at least 2 cm, entire or slightly emarginate, white or pink. Seeds c. 2 mm, rugose, not shining, with small strophiole not covering 1/3 of seed. 2n = 24. \bullet }{\i\fs28  C. Pyrenees.}{\fs28  Hs.
